Vehicle inspection and certification requirements add another layer of compliance complexity. Colorado requires annual safety inspections for commercial vehicles, but accessibility equipment inspections follow federal rather than state standards. This dual oversight system sometimes results in vehicles passing safety inspections while failing to meet ADA accessibility standards.

